MEDIA personalities Moshe Ndiki and Lillian Dube have joined Honey TV’s cooking show 7 Colours. According to the producers of the show, the two media personalities will go into the heart of South African homes to see families and friends flex their cooking skills to execute a full plate the best way they know how. Speaking to Daily Sun, veteran actress Lillian said she enjoyed being on set with Moshe as they worked well together. She said her favourite part of being on the show is going into people’s homes, interacting with them and seeing what their plates look like. Moshe, who is known for hosting controversial shows such as Uyang’thanda Na? and You Promised to Marry Me, said being part of this show was absolutely amazing. ALSO READ | NEW LEG FOR GP-MAORANGE Honey’s head of content Zinzi Velelo said the show brings something unique to the screen in a way that’s authentic. “We’re able to celebrate the best parts of our collective culture. It’s fun, it’s laid back and people get to be exactly who they are around something joyful – food,” she said. Honey’s commissioning editor Keneilwe Senyatsi described the show as fun and quirky. “It brings an exciting twist to traditional food shows,” she said. The show, 7 Colours, premieres on 17 February at 4.30pm on DStv Honey, DStv channel 173.